CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 18, 1961, pg. 10 reads: "Frogs Cite Rickmond - Charles Rickmond, standing, left center, was presented a plaque for meritorious service last Saturday by the Frogs Club in which organization he had served as secretary for 30 years. William (Buddy) Leftridge makes the presentation while other Frogs observe.  Seated, left to right, are: Dr. Charles F. Baltimore, Dr. Malvin Stockton, Harry Washington and Byron Peters.  Standing, left to right; Dr. Eugene Youngue, Dr. Robert Bolden, Alex Lee, Atty. Linn Washington, Dr. Earl Childs, Atty. Henry Smith Jr., president; Harold Jones, Edgar Milner, Ron Farrish, Francis Farmer, William Frederick, Percy A .Garland, William E. Graity and Dr. H.D.Primas. - Harris photo."
